      "date": "2011-11-10 12:18:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI don't think it should move into /proc/sys, since we have generally stopped locating new variables there.  Instead, it can be moved up one level to /proc/fs/lustre.\n\nAt some point, I'd like to duplicate all of the values in /proc/sys over to /proc/fs/lustre, and later remove them from /proc/sys entirely.  This would at least allow the Lustre code to avoid having to deal with two different types of system files internally.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7756d22644e72b182c42ab7a46156ecc2a13ee5d",
      "author": {
